What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string a = "hello";
    std::string b = std::move(a);
    std::cout << b << "\n";
    std::cout << a.empty() << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

The programmer expects a move but gets a copy instead. What is wrong?

